</prolog>
<conbody>
<p>The <keyword conref="wskc_conref-l0wskc04.dita#conref-l0wskc04/pcihsm2016mode"/> places certain
restrictions on the use of compliant-tagged key tokens. Thus, not all verbs can make use of such
keys. <xref href="wskc_pci_hsm_keys.dita#wskc_pci_hsm_keys/t_pci_hsm_impact_supp"/> provides a list
of <keyword conref="wskc_conref-l0wskc04.dita#conref-l0wskc04/pcihsm2016"/> compliant verbs.</p>
<p>Furthermore, you may want to migrate applications to work in <keyword
conref="wskc_conref-l0wskc04.dita#conref-l0wskc04/pcihsm2016mode"/>. This means, that you can adapt
existing applications prior to <keyword conref="wskc_conref-l0wskc04.dita#conref-l0wskc04/cca"/>
release 6.0 that exploit verbs that are now <keyword
conref="wskc_conref-l0wskc04.dita#conref-l0wskc04/pcihsm2016"/> compliant, to apply to <keyword
conref="wskc_conref-l0wskc04.dita#conref-l0wskc04/pcihsm2016mode"/>. For more information, see <xref
href="wskc_pci_hsm_migrate.dita#wskc_pci_hsm_migrate"/>.</p>
</conbody>
